description.narrative: In 2020, the Country Office contributed to the provision of adolescent- and youth-friendly services to 997,577 adolescents and youth (both in and out-of-school) through technical and financial support provided to 80 adolescent- and youth-dedicated health centres (SSU-SAJ). Thanks to the Country Office’s support, 23,844 adolescents and youths benefitted from an integrated package of prevention interventions, including HIV self-testing and pre-exposure prophylaxis (PrEP). In addition, 475,197 young people gained access to accurate HIV information through the U-Report platform. | Status:Partially met | As-of Date:27/01/2021
